{
  "stem": "5758.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And we were told that this was an area where a mass grave for the Spanish refugees when they caught-- there was a typhus [FRENCH] here.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And hundreds and hundreds of these refugees died there, and they were put into this grave, and they put this concrete block over it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had a friend there in the hospital, a Jewish doctor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And one day he said to me, you know, we are getting so much of the illnesses here, and we believe it's typhus.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We didn't get very much food there, and the-- we had-- we had started to get lice on our-- on our clothes and on our-- so I remembered a little bit that typhus come-- could come from lice.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I said, oh, this is not for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I must get out of here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "We were guarded by Sudanese soldiers from Sudan.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I knew then that my cousins from-- oh, one was in the camp, yeah, it was in-- in Saint-Cyprien with me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "That was Rosie's future husband, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And he told me that the Bodeks are living in Limoges, which was in-- in France, central France-- it was-- which I knew later on it was in the non-occupied zone.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Well, I-- at nighttime I said, I must leave there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "It wasn't so difficult, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "You didn't have to-- the Sudanese soldiers who guarded us-- we had wire.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "I cut-- I went through the wire and-- and left the-- left the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "It wasn't terribly difficult for a young fellow like me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And I knew that the nearest town was Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "So I said, I'm going to go direction of Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
